 Mr Mike Elliot, who’s at the lead of the rescue, has informed www.mobserver.co.za that the rescue teams are awaiting technicians from Johannesburg to come and repair the generator before operations can commence. New information about the discovery of seven more bodies within the shaft have been confirmed. Also read: Number of trapped people in mineshaft increases Mr Elliot disclosed that the intitial descent of recue teams allowed for the discovery. The bodies are roughly 1.5 kms underground from the shaft entrance and proto teams had made significant progress until the generator failed. He confirmed that the risk of an explosion is still a concern and that rescue teams will, under no circumstances, enter the shaft until ventilation has been restored.    Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za    